                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="abdicationcrisis_sng_1" hclass="sense"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="dis-g"><span class="wrap">(</span><span class="dtxt">in British history</span><span class="wrap">)</span></span></span> <span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a series of events in 1936, following King <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/edward-viii#edward_viii_topg_1" title="Edward VIII's definition"><span class="ndv">Edward VIII's</span></a> decision to marry a divorced American woman, <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/wallis-simpson" title="Wallis Simpson definition"><span class="ndv">Wallis Simpson</span></a>. It was thought that the British public would not accept a queen who had been divorced, and Edward was advised by the Prime Minister to <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/abdicate#abdicate_topg_1" title="abdicate definition"><span class="ndv">abdicate</span></a> <span class="gloss" htag="span" hclass="gloss">(= give up his position as king)</span>. The couple were married in France in 1937, and Edward's brother (as <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/george-vi" title="George VI definition"><span class="ndv">George VI</span></a>) became king in his place.</span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
